    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Cylinder Head And Valves - Valve
        Rotators And Retainer Keys - Testing Operation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="recondition" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Testing Operation</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid damage, lubricate the rotator with clean engine oil before testing and reuse in the
                    engine.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f12004103" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5206.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Testing Operation of Valve Rotators</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place valve spring and rotator in spring tester. Place a ball bearing between rotator and
                ram of the spring tester. The ball bearing must be large enough to prevent the ram from touching any
                part of the rotator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Paint a reference line on the rotator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compress the valve spring rapidly with even pressure and observe the rotator as it turns.
                Replace any rotator that does not turn.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
